More details here:&nbsp;<a href="http://bit.ly/AthleteTeamLead">http://bit.ly/AthleteTeamLead</a></p>
<p>
<u><strong>About opendorse</strong></u><br />
opendorse is an endorsement management platform that offers one-click endorsements to brands and professional athletes.</p>
<p>
The opendorse Athlete Team works with our athlete and agent users to maximize their use of the platform. In addition to working with current athletes and agents, the athlete team is responsible for discovering and developing new relationships with athletes and talent agencies.</p>
<p>
The Athlete Team Lead will manage the development and execution of a scalable customer acquisition strategy.</p>
<p>
<u>Market Research</u><br />
-Will be tasked with creating and implementing a market research strategy, identifying key market opportunities<br />
-Identify key indicator of athlete/agent&nbsp; - product fit<br />
-Discover partnership opportunities</p>
<p>
<u>Business Development</u>-Following discovery, lead will contact and develop relationship with agents<br />
-create marketing opportunity proposals for new and prospective agents</p>
<p>
<u>Marketing Team Integration</u><br />
-Assist marketing team in developing executing and measuring customer acquisition campaigns via digital media</p>
<br />
<p>
<u>Campaign Execution</u>-Assist in the execution of custom campaigns<br />
-Coordinate with brand team<br />
-Contact agents or athletes if necessary<br />
-Handle payment processing<br />
-Contract creation<br />
-Analytics reporting<br />
-Payment package creation and delivery</p>
<p>
<u>Support</u><br />
-Assist product team in supporting users<br />
-Provide detailed opportunity outline to product team for potential product features<br />
-Walk agents through platform</p>
<br />
<p>
<u>Customer Relationship Management</u>-Engage with current and prospective agent users<br />
-Provide product information to agent users<br />
-Create CRM software strategy</p>
<p>
<u>Management of Athlete/Agent Team</u><br />
-Manage hiring processes for athlete team members<br />
-Set goals for brand team members<br />
-Report brand team results to opendorse leadership team</p>
<br />
<p>
<u>Desired Skills</u>-2-3 years of talent agency experience<br />
-Sports marketing experience<br />
-Legal experience<br />
-Management experience</p>
<p>
<u>Perks</u><br />
-Full time position<br />
-Salary $36,000<br />
-Sales commission<br />
-Full health benefits<br />
-Short term long term disability<br />
-Dental and vision<br />
-Flexible work hours<br />
-Unlimited vacation</p>
